Dotfiles
========

Personal configuration files and a minimal installer for a lightweight i3-based
desktop and development environment.

Quick install
-------------

Clone and preview changes with a dry run:

```bash
git clone https://github.com/0xjah/Dotfiles.git ~/Dotfiles
cd ~/Dotfiles
chmod +x install.sh
./install.sh --dry-run
```

Apply the dotfiles (create backups and symlinks):

```bash
./install.sh --backup --symlink
```

Installer flags
---------------

- `--dry-run`  : show actions without modifying files
- `--backup`   : move existing targets to `~/.dotfiles_backup_<timestamp>/`
- `--symlink`  : create symlinks instead of copying files

Repository layout
------------------

Top-level and `.config/` directories contain component configs. Common
folders you may find here:

```
.config/i3  .config/polybar  .config/kitty  .config/nvim  .config/rofi
.config/dunst  .config/i3blocks  .config/picom  .zshrc  install.sh
```

Customization & usage
----------------------

- Edit the files in this repository to change configuration.
- Re-run `./install.sh --symlink` to update installed symlinks.
- Restore from backups in `~/.dotfiles_backup_<timestamp>/` if needed.

Contributing
------------

Issues and pull requests are welcome. Please open them on GitHub.

